data.title: "Exploring Jeju's Natural Wonders: A Week-Long Adventure"
data.description: "Exploring Jeju's Natural Wonders: A Week-Long Adventure" is a trip that takes place from 2025-01-18 to 2025-01-25. The trip includes visits to various tourist spots such as Hallasan National Park, Geomun Oreum, Witseoreum Volcanic Cone of Hallasan Mountain, Dodubong Peak, Eoseungsaengak Trail, 한라산국립공원 영실 탐방로, Seopseom, Oedolgae, Halla Eco Forest, Cheonjeyeon Waterfall, Soesokkak, Jeolmul Natural Recreation Forest, Seongsan Ilchulbong, and Jimibong. This trip offers a unique opportunity to experience the natural beauty and wonders of Jeju Island.

accomodations.Address: South Korea, Jeju-do, Cheju, Bonggae-dong, Myeongnim-ro, 575-107 제주특별자치도
accomodations.Description: Hanwha Resort Jeju is a tranquil island hotel located in South Korea, offering spacious and modern suites with two bedrooms, two showers, and toilets. The hotel features a restaurant, bar, and spa, as well as a mini-market and laundry facilities. Guests appreciate the hotel's convenient location, with easy access to key landmarks and attractions, including the Jeolmul forest and 4.3 memorial. The hotel is ideal for families and groups, with a playground and karaoke machines available for entertainment. The hotel has an overall rating of 4/5, with guests praising the cleanliness, comfort, and service quality. However, some guests have noted that the rooms need renovation and that the hotel is not the best value for the price.
accomodations.Name: Hanwha Resort Jeju

accomodations.Address: 47-7 Gwangnyeongpyeonghwa 8-gil, Aewol-eup, Cheju, Jeju-do, South Korea
accomodations.Description: 신성의숲(sacredforest) 명상리조트는 대한민국 제주특별자치도 제주시 애월읍 광령평화로 8길 47-7에 위치한 5/5 평점의 호텔입니다. 이 호텔은 명상과 휴식을 원하는 분들에게 이상적인 장소입니다. 객실은 편안하고 깨끗하며, 명상 및 요가 세션을 즐길 수 있는 전용 공간이 마련되어 있습니다. 호텔 주변에는 제주도의 아름다운 자연 경관이 펼쳐져 있어 산책이나 하이킹을 즐길 수 있습니다. 또한, 호텔 내에는 맛있는 음식을 즐길 수 있는 레스토랑과 카페도 있습니다. 신성의숲(sacredforest) 명상리조트는 제주국제공항에서 차로 20분 거리에 위치해 있어 교통이 편리하며, 제주도의 주요 관광지와도 가까워 여행객들에게 인기가 있습니다.
accomodations.Name: 신성의숲(sacredforest) 명상리조트

accomodations.Address: 229-7, 유수암리 애월읍 제주시 제주특별자치도 South Korea
accomodations.Description:
별담스테이는 제주특별자치도 제주시 애월읍 유수암리 229-7에 위치한 4.6/5 평점의 호텔입니다. 이 호텔은 아름다운 경치와 평화로운 분위기를 자랑하며, 가족, 커플, 비즈니스 여행객 모두에게 이상적인 선택입니다. 별담스테이는 아늑하고 편안한 객실을 제공하며, 호스트의 세심한 배려와 친절한 서비스로 손님들에게 좋은 평가를 받고 있습니다.

이 호텔은 주변 관광지와 교통편과의 접근성이 뛰어나며, 주요 랜드마크와 명소에 쉽게 접근할 수 있습니다. 또한, 별담스테이는 손님들에게 편안하고 청결한 환경을 제공하며, 객실 내 편의 시설과 다이닝 옵션을 통해 특별한 경험을 선사합니다.

별담스테이는 아름다운 경치와 평화로운 분위기, 그리고 훌륭한 서비스로 손님들에게 특별한 추억을 선사하는 호텔입니다.
accomodations.Name: 별담스테이

accomodations.Description: Donnaeko Pension is a 4.4/5-rated accommodation located at 28 Donnaeko-ro 67beon-gil, Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea. The hotel is ideal for families and couples seeking a comfortable and relaxing stay. The hotel offers cozy rooms with modern amenities, ensuring a pleasant experience for guests. The proximity to key landmarks and attractions, such as the nearby beach and local restaurants, makes it an excellent choice for travelers. The hotel's warm and friendly service, along with its overall value, makes Donnaeko Pension a standout option for those looking for a memorable stay in Jeju Island.
accomodations.Name: Donnaeko Pension

accomodations.Description: WE Hotel Jeju is a luxurious and upscale hotel located in Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea, offering stunning mountain or sea views from its polished rooms. Ideal for families, couples, and business travelers, the hotel boasts a spa, elegant dining options, and a range of complimentary classes such as aqua relaxing, Crystal bowl, and forest tours. The hotel's proximity to key landmarks and attractions, as well as its shuttle bus service to Jungmun, make it an excellent choice for a relaxing and rejuvenating stay. Guests can enjoy a variety of amenities, including heated pools, a private forest, and well-trained staff who are attentive and helpful. The hotel's overall value and unique characteristics, such as its focus on health and wellness, make it a standout choice for those seeking a peaceful and luxurious getaway in Jeju Island.
accomodations.Name: WE Hotel Jeju

accomodations.Description: Seogwipo Campa Jeju is a hotel located at 574-23 516-ro, Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea. While a brief description and overall rating are not available, it is an ideal choice for families and couples seeking a comfortable and relaxing stay. The hotel offers spacious rooms with modern amenities, ensuring a pleasant experience for guests. Its proximity to key landmarks and attractions, such as the Seogwipo Port and Jeju Island's beautiful beaches, makes it an excellent base for exploring the area. The hotel also boasts a restaurant serving local and international cuisine, providing guests with a variety of dining options. Overall, Seogwipo Campa Jeju offers great value for money and is a popular choice among travelers looking for a memorable stay in Jeju Island.
accomodations.Name: Seogwipo Campa Jeju

accomodations.Address: 2660 Haemajihaean-ro, Seongsan-eup, Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea
accomodations.Description: The Spring and Fall Resort, located at 2660 Haemajihaean-ro, Seongsan-eup, Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea, is a 4.2/5-rated hotel that is ideal for families with children. The hotel boasts an indoor playground and an indoor pool, making it a great choice for parents traveling with young kids. The rooms are spacious and clean, featuring a partial kitchen and some cookware, which is convenient for longer stays or budget-conscious travelers. The hotel also offers a breakfast service with tasty options, and the staff is helpful and accommodating. Guests appreciate the hotel's location and the overall value it provides. Some guests have mentioned that the hotel could improve its communication regarding facilities like the indoor pool and provide more information about the housekeeping schedule. However, the hotel's beautiful surroundings and high-quality services make it a great choice for a comfortable and enjoyable stay in Jeju.
accomodations.Name: Spring and Fall Resort

destinations.Description: Hallasan National Park, located in Jeju-do, South Korea, is a must-visit destination for nature lovers and adventure enthusiasts. With a 4.7/5 overall rating, this national park is renowned for its large mountain, featuring a variety of alpine plants and offering breathtaking views. Visitors can expect a challenging hike with steep stairs and a fair mix of rocks, making it ideal for those seeking an adrenaline rush. The park is also home to diverse wildlife, providing opportunities for wildlife encounters. With two restrooms and no water available, it's essential to plan your visit accordingly. The park's location near Jeju Island's key landmarks makes it easily accessible for tourists. Visitor experiences highlight the park's beauty, accessibility, and the rewarding path to the summit, where you can enjoy panoramic views of the island.
destinations.Name: Hallasan National Park

destinations.Address: South Korea, 제주특별자치도 제주시 조천읍 선흘리
destinations.Description: Geomun Oreum, a self-guided and assisted tour attraction, is an ancient volcanic crater located in Jeju Island, South Korea. With a 4.6/5 overall rating, visitors can expect a unique experience as they explore the crater's trees, caves, and scenic views. As a UNESCO natural heritage site, Geomun Oreum is a must-visit for nature lovers and history enthusiasts. The attraction offers three different trails, ranging from 1-3 hours in length, providing a variety of experiences for visitors. While some reviewers found the entrance fee to be pricey, many praised the peaceful atmosphere and the opportunity to learn about the site's significance as the "mother of Jeju" from knowledgeable tour guides. With its beautiful scenery and healing environment, Geomun Oreum is an ideal destination for those seeking a memorable and educational experience in Jeju Island.
destinations.Name: Geomun Oreum

destinations.Description:
Witseoreum Volcanic Cone of Hallasan Mountain, located in Seoho-dong, Seogwipo-si, Jeju-do, South Korea, is a natural landmark that offers visitors a unique and memorable experience. With a perfect 5/5 overall rating, this attraction is ideal for nature lovers and adventurers seeking scenic views and a chance to explore the island's geological history.

Visitors can expect to find a stunning volcanic cone formation, which is a rare and beautiful sight. The location of Witseoreum Volcanic Cone is convenient, as it is close to other popular landmarks in Jeju Island, making it easy to include in a larger itinerary.

Reviews from visitors highlight the beauty and accessibility of the attraction, with many praising the stunning views and the opportunity to learn about the island's volcanic history. The unique and rare wildlife found in the area is also a notable special feature, making Witseoreum Volcanic Cone a must-visit for nature enthusiasts and photographers.

In summary, Witseoreum Volcanic Cone of Hallasan Mountain is a natural landmark that offers visitors a chance to explore the island's geological history, enjoy stunning views, and encounter rare wildlife. Its ideal location and perfect overall rating make it a top choice for nature lovers and adventurers visiting Jeju Island.
destinations.Name: Witseoreum Volcanic Cone of Hallasan Mountain

destinations.Address: South Korea, Jeju-do, Cheju, 도두동 산1
destinations.Description: Dodubong Peak, located in Jeju-do, South Korea, is a highly-rated natural landmark with a 4.5/5 overall rating. Visitors can expect a short and safe climb to the peak, offering stunning 360-degree views of Jeju City, the sea, and Hallasan. The peak is particularly popular for plane spotting at Jeju Airport. Nature lovers and families will find this attraction ideal, as it offers a peaceful and scenic experience. The location is easily accessible and not crowded, making it a perfect spot for a leisurely hike. Visitors also appreciate the early cherry blossom bloomer surrounded by budding trees, adding to the attraction's natural beauty.
destinations.Name: Dodubong Peak

destinations.Address: South Korea, Jeju-do, Cheju, Haean-dong, 산 220-13
destinations.Description:
Eoseungsaengak Trail is a short, yet rewarding hiking trail located in Jeju Island, South Korea. This natural landmark offers visitors a chance to experience the beauty of the island's volcanic landscape while climbing up a volcanic cone. The trail is approximately 3 kilometers long and takes less than an hour for an average person to complete, with stunning views of Mount Hallasan and Jeju City awaiting at the summit.

The trail is not beginner-friendly, as it features lots of stairs and can be steep in some sections. However, it is still accessible to those who are reasonably fit and enjoy a moderate challenge. The hike starts at an elevation of around 980 meters and ends at 1169 meters, providing a great sampling of the full hike to the peak of Hallasan.

One of the highlights of the trail is the Japanese tunnel, where visitors can learn about the island's history and explore the dark, narrow passages where soldiers were once stationed. The trail is well-maintained, with gradual inclines and occasional steep sections that keep the hike interesting without being too strenuous.

Eoseungsaengak Trail is ideal for nature lovers, casual hikers, and those who want to enjoy the beauty of Hallasan without committing to a more intense trek. Visitors can expect to see stunning views of the surrounding nature, with the opportunity to spot rare wildlife and experience the unique flora and fauna of the region.

The trail's location in Jeju Island makes it easily accessible to tourists and locals alike. It is situated near other popular attractions, making it a great addition to a day of sightseeing or a longer hiking adventure. Visitors are encouraged to bring water and take breaks as needed, as the trail can be challenging in certain sections.

Overall, Eoseungsaengak Trail is a must-visit attraction for anyone looking to experience the natural beauty of Jeju Island. With its stunning views, historical significance, and moderate challenge, it offers a memorable and rewarding experience for visitors of all ages and skill levels.
destinations.Name: Eoseungsaengak Trail

destinations.Address: 246 Yeongsil-ro, Jungmun-dong, Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea
destinations.Description: Hanla Mountain National Park's Yeongsil Trail is a must-visit hiking destination in Jeju Island, offering breathtaking views in all seasons. Located at 246 Yeongsil-ro, Jungmun-dong, Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea, this 4.8/5-rated attraction boasts a rest area and a shelter for visitors. The trail is known for its scenic beauty, with reviewers praising its stunning views of Hallasan National Park and the challenge it presents to hikers of all levels. Visitors can expect a medium difficulty hike with plenty of stairs and a gradual pace, taking about an hour to reach Byeongpung Rock. The trail is ideal for nature lovers and adventurers, with reviewers recommending good walking shoes, a windbreaker, and plenty of water. The top offers amazing views and beautiful nature, making it a perfect spot for drone recordings. However, visitors should be prepared for the exhausting path upwards and allow 2-3 hours for the hike.
destinations.Name: 한라산국립공원 영실 탐방로

destinations.Description: Known as Jeju Island, เกาะเซจู is a popular tourist destination located in Jeju-si, Jeju-do, South Korea. With an overall rating of 4.5/5, this natural landmark offers visitors a chance to experience the beauty of its scenic views and unique geological formations. Visitors can expect to see diverse wildlife, including rare species of plants and animals, and participate in various outdoor activities such as hiking and birdwatching. The island is ideal for nature lovers, families, and adventure seekers alike. Its proximity to key landmarks and other popular places in Jeju Island makes it easily accessible for tourists. Visitor experiences often highlight the island's tranquility, picturesque landscapes, and the opportunity to connect with nature. With its rich biodiversity and unique ecosystem, เกาะเซจู is a must-visit attraction for anyone looking to explore the natural wonders of Jeju Island.
destinations.Name: เกาะเซจู

destinations.Address: South Korea, Jeju-do, Seogwipo, 특별자치도, 송산동 산1-1 KR
destinations.Description: Seopseom, located in South Korea's Jeju-do, Seogwipo, is a highly-rated tourist attraction with an overall rating of 4.8/5. This natural landmark is ideal for nature lovers and adventure seekers, offering breathtaking views and a unique diving experience. Visitors can expect to see stunning scenery and engage in various outdoor activities. The attraction's proximity to the Orba Cafe provides an additional perk, as the view from the cafe's second floor is a popular spot for photography. Seopseom's special feature is its status as a top diving spot, making it a must-visit for adventure enthusiasts. The attraction's reviews highlight its beauty and the memorable experiences it offers, with visitors praising the misty island's scenic views and the unique diving opportunities.
destinations.Name: Seopseom

destinations.Description: Oedolgae is a scenic lookout point in Jeju Island, South Korea, offering dramatic cliffside views and a network of trails for exploration. Visitors can expect to see stunning rock formations, clear blue waters, and opportunities for swimming. This attraction is ideal for families, nature lovers, and adventure seekers looking for a peaceful and tranquil experience. Located in Seogwipo, Oedolgae is easily accessible and offers a unique perspective of the island's natural beauty. With a 4.4/5 overall rating, visitors have praised the area for its impressive rock formations, beautiful coastal views, and well-maintained trails. The nearby grass lawn and benches provide a perfect spot for relaxation and meditation, making Oedolgae a must-visit spot for anyone traveling to Jeju Island.
destinations.Name: Oedolgae

destinations.Address: South Korea, Jeju-do, Cheju, 특별자치도, 516-ro, 2596 KR
destinations.Description: Halla Eco Forest, located in Jeju-do, South Korea, is a highly-rated natural attraction with an overall rating of 4.5/5. Visitors can expect a vast forest with various zones, including a pond and wild fruit trees, where they can observe a variety of bird species. The forest is known for its fragrant pine trees and offers several hiking trails with ample resting spots. It is particularly beautiful in the spring and is ideal for families, nature lovers, and adventurers. The forest is easily accessible by bus and is situated near a horse pasture and Jeolmul Recreational Forest. Visitors appreciate the well-maintained trails and the peaceful atmosphere, making it a memorable experience for all.
destinations.Name: Halla Eco Forest

destinations.Address: South Korea, Jeju-do, Cheju, 연동 산110-1
destinations.Description: Geomeun Oreum is a must-visit natural landmark in Jeju Island, South Korea. Located in Cheju, 연동 산110-1, this attraction boasts a 4.5/5 overall rating and is ideal for nature lovers and families. Visitors can expect breathtaking scenic views, hiking trails, and a serene atmosphere. The proximity to other popular landmarks in Jeju Island makes it a convenient stop for tourists. Reviewers often highlight the beauty and tranquility of the place, making it a memorable experience for all. With its unique landscape and seasonal events, Geomeun Oreum is a hidden gem that should not be missed.
destinations.Name: Geomeun Oreum

destinations.Address: 2232 Jungmun-dong, 특별자치도, Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea
destinations.Description:
Cheonjeyeon Waterfall, a natural landmark located in Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea, is a must-visit attraction for nature lovers and adventure seekers. With a 4.3/5 overall rating, this storied, 3-tier waterfall cascades from a cave, surrounded by lush greenery, offering visitors a chance to escape the heat and enjoy a scenic path through the forest. The waterfall is accessible via numerous stairs, so visitors should be prepared for a moderate hike.

The waterfall's location near various landmarks in Jeju Island makes it an ideal stop for families, adventurers, and photography enthusiasts. Visitors can expect to see a beautiful temple, a nicely decorated bridge, and a cheap entrance fee. The waterfall's special feature is its unique landscape, which is best experienced during the summer months.

Reviews highlight the waterfall's beauty, accessibility, and the challenge of the numerous stairs. Visitors can enjoy the nice walking trails to the falls, but should be aware that the third fall may be difficult for kids and elderly. The waterfall's unique landscape and the opportunity to see a beautiful temple and a nicely decorated bridge make it a memorable experience for all visitors.
destinations.Name: Cheonjeyeon Waterfall

destinations.Description: Soesokkak, a scenic estuary located in Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea, is a popular natural landmark known for its cliffs of volcanic rock and serene atmosphere. Visitors can enjoy kayaking and traditional raft rides, with many praising the 20-minute kayaking experience as a must-do activity. The estuary's unique brackish water, formed by the meeting of fresh groundwater and seawater, adds to its charm. With a 4.2/5 overall rating and numerous 5/5 reviews, Soesokkak is highly recommended for families, nature lovers, and adventure seekers alike. Its proximity to other popular Jeju Island landmarks makes it an ideal addition to any travel itinerary.
destinations.Name: Soesokkak

destinations.Description: Jeolmul Natural Recreation Forest is a tranquil park located in Jeju Island, South Korea, offering visitors a serene escape amidst a dense cedar forest. The park features well-maintained hiking trails suitable for all skill levels, including the popular Neonadri-gil trail, which offers stunning views of the surrounding landscape. Visitors can also enjoy picnicking, playing in the playgrounds, and exploring the volcanic hill, Jeonmul oreum. The park is highly recommended for nature lovers, families, and adventurers seeking a peaceful retreat. With a 4.6/5 overall rating, visitors praise the park's scenic beauty, well-maintained trails, and cooling atmosphere, making it an ideal destination for a hot afternoon.
destinations.Name: Jeolmul Natural Recreation Forest

destinations.Address: 78 Seongsan-ri, Seongsan-eup, Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea
destinations.Description: Seongsan Ilchulbong, a renowned volcanic cone in Jeju Island, is a must-visit natural landmark with a bowl-shaped crater and a popular hiking route. Located in Seongsan-ri, Seongsan-eup, Seogwipo, Jeju-do, South Korea, this attraction boasts an overall rating of 4.6/5 and is ideal for families, adventurers, and nature lovers. Visitors can expect stunning views, a paid entry, and a unique hiking experience with well-maintained paths and resting spots. The summit offers breathtaking panoramic views of the surrounding landscape, making it a perfect spot for photography enthusiasts. Additionally, there are free areas with great views towards the summit and a tiny temple. For Korean visitors, there are culture and nature guides available on the top who can provide interesting information about the summit, Jeju culture, nature, and amazing stories. Seongsan Ilchulbong is easily accessible and close to other popular places in Jeju Island, making it a perfect addition to any travel itinerary.
destinations.Name: Seongsan Ilchulbong

destinations.Address: South Korea, Jeju-do, Cheju, Gujwa-eup, Jongdal-ri, 266 제주특별자치도
destinations.Description: Jimibong, located in Jeju-do, South Korea, is a highly-rated natural landmark that offers visitors a low-key hiking experience with stunning views. With an overall rating of 4.6/5, this attraction is ideal for nature lovers and families seeking a scenic adventure. The hike to the top takes approximately 15 minutes and is well-maintained, making it accessible for beginners. Visitors can expect breathtaking panoramic views from the summit, which is a popular spot for photography. The location of Jimibong is conveniently close to other key landmarks in Jeju Island, making it a perfect addition to any travel itinerary. Visitor reviews highlight the beauty and accessibility of the hike, with many describing the view from the top as "amazing" and "one of the best views ever."
destinations.Name: Jimibong
